1
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:52,039
What are the chances of my grandmother surviving?

2
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:56,360
Right now, it looks like it's about 10%.

3
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:06,120
Doctor,

4
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,240
I beg you.

5
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:09,400
Don't do this. Get up.

6
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,720
Please save my grandmother.

7
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:11,240
Yuanbao,

8
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:12,240
get up first.

9
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:15,480
I beg you to save my grandmother, doctor.

10
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,320
Doctor, please.

11
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:18,360
Whatever it takes,

12
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,520
you must save her.

13
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:21,079
Get up first.

14
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:22,560
Get up.

15
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,480
Rest assured,

16
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:26,680
we will do our best.

17
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,840
Even if there's only a 1% chance,

18
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,440
we won't give up.

19
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,079
But

20
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:34,840
this surgery is quite difficult,

21
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:37,320
and the treatment costs are not low.

22
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:39,200
You must be mentally prepared.

23
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,880
My family needs money urgently.

24
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:50,520
Can you lend me some?

25
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,640
Okay. It's fine.

26
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:56,920
Thank you.

27
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,360
Dandan,

28
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:04,400
Are you well off right now?

29
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,900
Can you lend me some money?

30
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,840
Any amount is fine.

31
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:27,280
Are you in pain, Grandma?

32
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,930
The doctor said this disease is very painful.

33
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:34,200
I wish I could bear the pain for you.

34
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:37,079
You have to get better.

35
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,570
We're all waiting for you to come home.

36
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:59,079
Time to get up, sleepyhead.

37
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:06,640
Grandma.

38
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,320
Grandma.

39
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:15,640
Grandma.

40
00:04:18,279 --> 00:04:19,560
Weren't you...

41
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:25,720
Grandma.

42
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:27,840
Grandma.

43
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:55,880
Jingu.

44
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:57,720
Yuanbao.

45
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:00,100
My uncle is a cardiovascular doctor.

46
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,680
He's very famous in Beijing.

47
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:02,920
I've already told him.

48
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,160
Maybe he can help.

49
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,360
Really?

50
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:07,640
That's great.

51
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,680
Thank you, deskmate.

52
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:12,040
What should I do now?

53
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,520
You're welcome.

54
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:15,690
But my uncle is usually quite busy.

55
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:17,090
What we discussed is

56
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,520
you first make a copy of Grandma's medical report

57
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:21,320
and mail it directly to my uncle.

58
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,680
Let him take a look first

59
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:24,640
to see if there's a better treatment plan.

60
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:26,280
If she can be transferred to Beijing,

61
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:28,480
there might be a greater hope for a cure.

62
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,160
Okay.

63
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,320
Thank you.

64
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:33,080
I'll go make a copy of the report right now.

65
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,240
To make it faster,

66
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,560
I'll send you the mailing address in a bit.

67
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,800
Use expedited shipping.

68
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,400
He should receive it the day after tomorrow.

69
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:39,880
Okay.

70
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:40,800
Okay. Thank you.

71
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,400
Thank you. Thank you so much.

72
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,159
You asked Mu Qingyun to enter the competition,

73
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,420
but he flatly refused.

74
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:55,280
Now Yuanbao's family is in trouble again.

75
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:56,080
Meng Jingu,

76
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:57,320
you should go.

77
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:59,450
You'll do fine in the competition.

78
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:01,940
And you even have a chance to win first place.

79
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:04,890
May I come in?

80
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,840
Mu Qingyun, why are you here?

81
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,160
Mr. Tian,

82
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:14,840
I have decided to participate in the National Physics Competition.

83
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,960
Are you willing to admit it?

84
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,770
I've made up my mind.

85
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,440
But we just...

86
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,970
convinced Meng Jingu to go.

87
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:29,400
Meng Jingu,

88
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,160
you decide.

89
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,320
Have you thought it through?

90
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,360
Yuanbao...

91
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:39,090
I've made up my mind.

92
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,720
As long as it can save Grandma,

93
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,920
I'll do anything.

94
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,880
It's been hard on you.

95
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:44,930
As for the money,

96
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,650
we'll figure something out together.

97
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,920
Qingyun, I'm here in the UK,

98
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,720
and I've visited many hospitals.

99
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:13,920
The conclusion so far

100
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,680
is that they don't recommend transferring Grandma.

101
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,600
Don't worry, I'll keep looking.

102
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:19,560
If I can't find a doctor in the UK,

103
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,160
I'll look in other countries.

104
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:23,080
Someone must be able to cure Grandma.

105
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:23,880
Yes.

106
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:26,000
Someone will be able to cure Grandma.

107
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,120
I can't give up,

108
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,540
and I can't break down.

109
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,160
Yuanbao needs me right now.

110
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,600
I have to be strong

111
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,600
and take care of her for Grandma.

112
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,640
You're back.

113
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,240
Um...

114
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:51,680
Well, I made some dishes.

115
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:52,780
Go wash your hands.

116
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,800
Where are my mom and grandpa?

117
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:59,760
They need to stay at the hospital a bit longer.

118
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:01,020
They'll be back later.

119
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,840
What made you want to cook today?

120
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,400
I was just thinking,

121
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:08,880
since you guys are going to the hospital all day

122
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:10,760
and I can't really help with anything,

123
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:13,280
I'd cook some dishes for you.

124
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:17,480
Don't just stand there. Go wash your hands and eat.

125
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,600
We can take some to my mom later.

126
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,000
I also want to see Grandma.

127
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,080
You burned yourself.

128
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:32,000
It's my first time cooking. Everyone gets burned,

129
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:32,720
right?

130
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:44,440
Yuanbao.

131
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,680
I'm sorry.

132
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:51,720
Yuanbao.

133
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,560
I really didn't mean it.

134
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:54,620
No need to explain.

135
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:56,610
It's in the past.

136
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:04,600
All right. Keep it dry tonight,

137
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:07,620
and apply some ointment yourself tomorrow.

138
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:12,560
Yuanbao.

139
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:14,400
What's wrong?

140
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:16,400
Ever since Grandma was hospitalized,

141
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:18,460
have you not had a good night's sleep?

142
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:34,000
Yuanbao,

143
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,530
why are you so stubborn?

144
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:38,080
Just let me go to the hospital with you.

145
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:39,740
I haven't seen Grandma today.

146
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,400
No need.

147
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,520
Your hand is injured, and it's raining outside.

148
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,960
I can go by myself.

149
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,280
With such heavy rain outside,

150
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:47,000
I definitely can't let you go alone, Yuanbao.

151
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,260
Just let me go with you.

152
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,720
Right now,

153
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,260
you feel like a stranger to me.

154
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,840
I want to go by myself.

155
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:08,560
Yuanbao.

156
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:11,080
Don't forget to tell Grandma

157
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:13,560
that I'll be waiting for her at home.

158
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:15,880
Okay, I got it.

159
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,320
Be safe on your way, Yuanbao.

160
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:31,560
You want me to sell the house now?

161
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:33,360
Are you crazy?

162
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:35,170
If we sell the house,

163
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,840
where will Qingyun and I live?

164
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,970
Do you expect us to live under a bridge?

165
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,800
I never said I wouldn't care.

166
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,080
And I never said we shouldn't get treatment.

167
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:45,240
But do you know what the doctor said?

168
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:47,000
The chance of Grandma surviving now

169
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,240
is only ten percent.

170
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:50,600
Do you know what that means?

171
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:53,040
It means it's highly likely that in the end,

172
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,880
we will lose both her and our money.

173
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:56,610
I have no conscience? Mu Dabai,

174
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,440
has your conscience been eaten by dogs?

175
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,100
How could you say such a thing?

176
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:00,840
Fine.

177
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:03,320
Since you insist on bringing up the past today,

178
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:05,160
I'll spell it out for you.

179
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:09,360
We were supposed to be on duty the day of the incident.

180
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:10,800
But Qingyun suddenly got

181
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:12,960
acute pneumonia and had to be hospitalized.

182
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:15,760
That's why we swapped shifts with the couple.

183
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:17,600
We didn't do it on purpose.

184
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,360
We didn't know an accident would happen that day,

185
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,280
right?

186
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,560
Besides,

187
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:24,320
many things are just fate.

188
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,000
It's been so many years,

189
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,880
and we've done all we should do.

190
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,880
What else do you want from me?

191
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:32,480
Do we really have to pay with our lives

192
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,760
to make it right?

193
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,000
Yuanbao.

194
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:50,840
Is it true?

195
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,000
I...

196
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:53,520
I...

197
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:54,760
I...

198
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:56,320
That day,

199
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,620
they shouldn't have died.

200
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:01,360
Right?

201
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:02,960
I...

202
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,080
Yuanbao,

203
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,840
let me explain.

204
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:10,480
We...

205
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:12,920
we didn't mean to hide it from you.

206
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:17,120
No.

207
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:20,640
How could this happen?

208
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,280
Why did this happen?

209
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:28,840
Yuanbao.

210
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,980
I'll leave the factory to you.

211
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:12,560
How is it?

212
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:14,560
I need to go to the factory.

213
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:16,080
It's so late. I'll go with you.

214
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:16,840
Let's go.

215
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:28,080
You're back.

216
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:30,080
Why didn't you answer the phone?

217
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,040
I was so worried.

218
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,480
You brought an umbrella.

219
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,010
How did you still get so wet?

220
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:37,400
I'm fine.

221
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,200
How are you fine?

222
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,160
You are completely soaked.

223
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:41,200
Come on, let me help you change your clothes.

224
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,240
Leave me alone.

225
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:47,240
Yuanbao.

226
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,760
What's wrong?

227
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:52,040
I said I'm fine.

228
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,250
Go back and get some rest early.

229
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:04,760
Yuanbao.

230
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:06,580
Then remember to dry your hair

231
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,200
and take some cold medicine.

232
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,370
You're still awake.

233
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:24,600
Mom, why are you back so late?

234
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,890
I stayed with Grandma a bit longer.

235
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:36,120
Is Yuanbao back?

236
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:46,080
Go to bed early.

237
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:56,960
Did you get enough money

238
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:00,560
for Grandma's medical bills?

239
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,090
It's none of your business.

240
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:05,760
Just focus on your studies.

241
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:07,720
Mom,

242
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:09,800
I mean,

243
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:11,690
I still have some pocket money.

244
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:20,930
What do you mean?

245
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:24,400
You're just like your father.

246
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:26,119
Besides pressuring me,

247
00:17:26,119 --> 00:17:27,640
what else can you two do?

248
00:17:28,319 --> 00:17:29,760
Mom, I mean...

249
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:31,920
Mu Qingjun, look at yourself!

250
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:34,160
You're not making progress in your studies,

251
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:36,120
and you can't take care of yourself.

252
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:37,650
You're almost 20 years old.

253
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:39,080
For this family,

254
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:40,640
I cook for you,

255
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:41,960
I go to work,

256
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:44,200
and I have to take care of everyone.

257
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:47,480
We've been carrying a blood debt for you for over a decade.

258
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:50,680
Even selling our house and land isn't enough to pay it off.

259
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:53,080
What more do you want from us?

260
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,720
Mom, what does this mean?

261
00:18:08,280 --> 00:18:09,920
You... you just said,

262
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:11,960
for me?

263
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:12,960
No.

264
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:14,880
Did I hear that right, Mom?

265
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:15,700
It's not...

266
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:16,320
It's not...

267
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:17,650
It's not like that, son.

268
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,080
I just...

269
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,960
It's not about Yuanbao

270
00:18:26,560 --> 00:18:28,240
and Grandma, is it?

271
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,640
No, no, no.

272
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,440
I'm sorry, son. No.

273
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:32,960
Mom was too harsh.

274
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,160
I didn't mean that.

275
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:35,080
I mean...

276
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:36,360
No, I...

277
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,360
No, I'm just under too much pressure.

278
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:40,160
I... I don't know...

279
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,600
No. I'm sorry, son.

280
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:43,640
Don't...

281
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:45,920
Is it about Uncle Xiong and the others?

282
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:51,040
No.

283
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:54,080
No, it's not.

284
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,240
So,

285
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:03,330
the death of Uncle Xiong and Auntie back then,

286
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:08,040
did it have to do with you

287
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:11,640
and Dad, right?

288
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:15,960
We didn't mean to do it.

289
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:20,120
We really didn't mean to.

290
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:22,520
Not on purpose.

291
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:25,320
We didn't mean it.

292
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:27,040
We didn't mean it.

293
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,760
We didn't mean it.

294
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:33,160
We didn't mean it.

295
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:40,280
We didn't mean it.

296
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:43,680
We didn't mean it.

297
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:51,160
Actually, that day,

298
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,420
your father and I were supposed to be on duty.

299
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,880
But because you suddenly got acute pneumonia,

300
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,000
we had to take you to the hospital.

301
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:03,480
So we swapped shifts with Yuanbao's parents.

302
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:05,760
But we never expected

303
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:08,560
that an accident would happen that day.

304
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,080
Yuanbao.

305
00:21:59,000 --> 00:21:59,800
Yuanbao.

306
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:02,300
Auntie, yesterday...

307
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:04,920
I...

308
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:05,760
Auntie,

309
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:08,000
I figured it out.

310
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,080
I don't blame you.

311
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:15,410
And I don't blame Mutou.

312
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:20,600
Really?

313
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:24,720
It was an accident after all.

314
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:27,290
You didn't do it on purpose.

315
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:29,520
And Mutou is innocent too.

316
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:31,250
If there's anyone to blame,

317
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:35,160
it's my parents' bad luck.

318
00:22:36,360 --> 00:22:37,000
No.

319
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:40,000
It's us.

320
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,440
It's our bad luck.

321
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:45,960
Don't say that.

322
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,640
What bad luck?

323
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:50,200
I won't allow you to think like that.

324
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:51,960
Auntie,

325
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:56,760
thank you and Uncle for

326
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:59,860
taking care of me and my grandma all these years.

327
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:02,120
Without you,

328
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:07,240
we wouldn't have had such a stable life for so long.

329
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,160
But now,

330
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,460
I don't want to be a burden to you anymore.

331
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,760
You're still blaming us,

332
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:20,720
and hating us,

333
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:23,080
aren't you?

334
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:26,160
Auntie,

335
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:28,330
all these years,

336
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:32,090
even though I've always called you Aunt Ning,

337
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:33,880
in my heart,

338
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:36,080
I've already treated you

339
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:37,680
just like my own mother.

340
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:42,840
I just said,

341
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:44,720
I don't blame you.

342
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:47,000
You've been so good to us.

343
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:48,840
If I blame you

344
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:50,280
or hate you,

345
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:53,490
I wouldn't deserve to be a human being.

346
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:56,040
Silly girl.

347
00:23:58,240 --> 00:23:59,520
I've already treated you

348
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:01,640
as my own daughter in my heart.

349
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:05,400
Yesterday,

350
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,160
I was just,

351
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:12,040
just complaining to your uncle.

352
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:14,400
I didn't mean it.

353
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:16,880
But you have to believe me,

354
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:18,640
I never felt

355
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,570
you and your grandma were burdens.

356
00:24:21,520 --> 00:24:23,200
We are family.

357
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:36,050
The medical bills I owe you,

358
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:38,180
I'll find a way to pay you back.

359
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:48,200
By the way,

360
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:50,440
as for Mutou,

361
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:53,360
please don't tell him.

362
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:56,250
I'm afraid it will affect his studies.

363
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:58,000
I'm going to class.

364
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:00,680
Qingyun already knows.

365
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:23,690
Strive for the college entrance exam.

366
00:25:31,920 --> 00:25:34,240
The best thing about childhood sweethearts

367
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:35,640
is exactly this.

368
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:39,720
There's always an unspoken understanding that others wouldn't get.

369
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:42,480
Regarding what happened to his parents and mine,

370
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,640
I know he knows,

371
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:46,840
and he knows I understand.

372
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:49,800
But neither of us confronted the other,

373
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:52,560
to avoid any awkwardness.

374
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:57,760
Yuanbao.

375
00:25:58,240 --> 00:26:00,700
Actually, I really want to apologize to you.

376
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,920
If it weren't for my illness,

377
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:05,770
nothing would have happened to your parents.

378
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:08,600
All the pain and suffering you went through

379
00:26:09,920 --> 00:26:11,840
should have happened to me.

380
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,240
But now,

381
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:15,280
even if I say

382
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:16,960
a casual 'sorry,'

383
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:19,200
what's the point?

384
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:28,880
After that day,

385
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:31,940
Yuanbao has been deliberately avoiding us.

386
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:36,080
My mom and I didn't know

387
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:38,650
how to salvage this relationship either.

388
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:40,200
Many times,

389
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:43,720
the more afraid you are of losing, the less you dare to try and salvage it.

390
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:46,440
Without experiencing this feeling firsthand,

391
00:26:46,840 --> 00:26:48,240
no one could understand.

392
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:52,360
Ma'am,

393
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,880
this house of yours is really too old,

394
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:56,320
and the location is poor.

395
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:58,560
It's too difficult for you to sell it so urgently.

396
00:26:58,560 --> 00:27:00,360
How about you think it over?

397
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:23,440
The hospital expenses are draining like water every day.

398
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:27,160
The money we borrowed is almost gone.

399
00:27:28,360 --> 00:27:29,880
Even though I refused her,

400
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:31,400
she still stubbornly

401
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:33,600
sold all her jewelry.

402
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:36,120
And she still goes to the hospital

403
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:38,250
to see grandma every day without fail.

404
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:41,520
How do we weigh right and wrong in many things?

405
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:00,760
How is it, deskmate?

406
00:28:00,760 --> 00:28:01,760
Any news?

407
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:06,120
Yuanbao.

408
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:08,400
I'm sorry.

409
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:10,280
My uncle,

410
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:12,000
he said

411
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:16,880
the treatment plan and advice they gave

412
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:19,810
are pretty much the same as the conclusion

413
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,860
from Jinghai People's Hospital.

414
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:27,320
Yuanbao.

415
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:29,180
Don't be like this.

416
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:32,640
I've made up my mind.

417
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:34,800
Tomorrow I'll ask Mr. Tian for a leave and go to Beijing.

418
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:35,480
I'll beg my uncle in person.

419
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:36,880
That won't be necessary.

420
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:38,480
Thank you, deskmate.

421
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:40,760
Don't say that.

422
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:43,200
I couldn't even help you.

423
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:46,480
I feel really bad about it.

424
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:48,690
You've worked really hard.

425
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:51,040
I am truly grateful to you.

426
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:52,840
Actually,

427
00:28:54,840 --> 00:28:56,700
my father also got sick recently.

428
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:00,480
What illness?

429
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:05,080
Liver cancer.

430
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:19,800
We both need to be strong,

431
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:21,040
okay?

432
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:35,320
Dr. Wang, Dr. Wang!

433
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:37,540
Something is wrong with the patient!

434
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:39,000
Grandma!

435
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:12,290
Doctor, how is the patient?

436
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:15,400
The patient's condition suddenly worsened during the surgery.

437
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,200
I'm afraid

438
00:30:16,520 --> 00:30:18,450
he won't make it through the night.

439
00:31:18,280 --> 00:31:19,560
How is Grandpa Gong?

440
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:22,530
His blood pressure is high.

441
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,970
He is getting an IV drip in the ward now.

442
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:26,970
After all, he is old,

443
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:28,820
and can't handle such things.

444
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:37,530
The burial plot has been arranged,

445
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:39,440
right next to Tiejun and Aihua.

446
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,320
Yuanbao.

447
00:31:51,280 --> 00:31:53,520
I'm here, Grandma.
